in South Korea through our consulate-general or embassy but the 
government is not accepting them in order not to get on the 
nerves of North Korea." 
  "The government's position on the matter remains the same as 
before and the government is not considering bringing in the 
North Koreans at the moment," the chief executive was quoted as 
