<DOCNO> FBIS4-4967 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas066_c_94033" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-066 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   WPK Group Leaves for Greece; Arts Troupes Arrive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    WPK Group Leaves for Greece; Arts Troupes Arrive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0504231794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1515 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0504231794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the 
Workers' Party of Korea headed by vice department director of 
the WPK Central Committee Pak Kyong-son left here today to 
participate in the Third Congress of the Panhellenic Socialist 
Movement of Greece. 
  Malaysian musicians, Mongolian art and acrobatic groups, a 
Bangladesh art group, a Chinese acrobatic group, a Colombian 
musician and Vietnamese musicians came here today to participate 
in the 12th April spring friendship art festival. Also arriving 
here today was a delegation of the Kim Chong-suk kindergarten in 
Dalandzadgad City, Omnogov Province, Mongolia, led by its 
superintendent Altantuya. 

</TEXT>

