<H3> <TI>   Ozawa Says Import Targets `Possible' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ozawa Says Import Targets `Possible' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504115194 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0504115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ichiro Ozawa, Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] 
secretary general, said that Japan should work flexibly on 
measures to break the deadlock in the Japanese-U.S. economic 
framework talks. He noted that it may be possible for Japan to 
set import targets as long as these are not linked to U.S. 
sanctions. 
  In a 4 April news conference at the Diet, Ozawa said, "I 
think that Japan should take the initiative in improving its 
market practices so that these are not criticized by the 
international community." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

