<H3> <TI>   SDPJ Member Proposes Visit to North Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ Member Proposes Visit to North Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504141394 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0504141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It was disclosed on 4 April that one of the members 
of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] delegation (led 
by SDPJ Vice Chairman Issei Inoue) to China contacted a 
high-ranking official at the DPRK (North Korean) Embassy during 
their stay in Beijing from 1 to 3 April. An SDPJ source said 
that SDPJ upper house member Hajime Fukada met with the North 
Korean Embassy official in Beijing and proposed that a 
delegation of coalition Diet members visit North Korea. The 
North Korean official reportedly demonstrated a positive 
reaction to Fukada's proposal. 
  Inoue said at the 4 April news conference that he told 
Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen on 2 April that the SDPJ 
supports the UN Security Council [UNSC] presidential statement 
on the North Korean nuclear development issue and that it 
attaches importance to cooperation with the United Nations. He 
added he had told Qian that "the SDPJ will abide by the UN 
policy as one of the Japanese ruling parties." Inoue then 
demonstrated an eagerness to promote diplomatic activities 
between ruling party lawmakers to solve the issue at the 
interparty "diplomatic forum" to be set up on 5 April. 

</TEXT>

