<H3> <TI>   Official Views Possibility of War in Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Views Possibility of War in Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604040194 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 6 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0604040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 5 April Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] Vice Foreign Minister Kunihiko Saito appeared on a 
TV Asahi program on 5 April, during which he commented on the 
DPRK's development of nuclear weapons. With regard to the 
possibility of armed conflict on the Korean peninsula in the 
near future, Saito stated: "We cannot discount such a 
possibility, and must take an optimistic view of the situation." 
However, he added: "It will not be good for the North Koreans 
to feel that Japan's thinking is premised on the possibility of 
armed conflict." He stressed North Korea should not be provoked. 

