<H3> <TI>   Defense Agency Chief Voices Concern on DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Agency Chief Voices Concern on DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604043994 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 5 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0604043994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 5 April Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] At an 5 April news conference, Defense Agency 
Director General Kazuo Aichi commented on the situation on the 
Korean peninsula, which has become tense over the DPRK's (North 
Korea) suspected nuclear development, stating: "There is an 
increasing possibility that the worst will occur. We should be 
more strained and should be ready." He thus indicated that the 
situation could become more serious depending on North Korea's 
future actions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

