<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa's Resignation Remark Termed `Reckless' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hosokawa's Resignation Remark Termed `Reckless' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604041994 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 6 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0604041994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 6 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] At a 3 April dinner, Prime Minister Hosokawa made a 
remark indicating his wish to resign. 
  Commenting on the prime minister's remark while speaking 
with 
a group of reporters early in the morning of 6 April, Deputy 
Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Hatoyama said: "The prime 
minister made the remark at a dinner. He made the statement 
from his position as a civilian, not as prime minister. He is 
used to speaking his mind to others." But Hatoyama added: "As 
prime minister, he made a reckless remark. I believe he did not 
make that statement even jokingly." 

</TEXT>

