<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Chief Suggests Shakeup in Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Chief Suggests Shakeup in Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604061294 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 6 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0604061294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 5 April Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] At a news conference held after the cabinet meeting 
on 5 April, Director General of the Defense Agency Kazuo Aichi 
stated: "Each cabinet has a role to play. The Tanaka cabinet 
dealt with the restoration of diplomatic relations between Japan 
and China, and the Takeshita cabinet with consumption taxes. 
The Hosokawa cabinet has accomplished its mission of political 
reform. It will naturally have to change its character and set 
its next goal. Depending on what the goal will be, the question 
of whether the present framework is good enough may arise." He 
indicated that in order to facilitate the implementation of tax 
reform, which is expected to follow the passage of the fiscal 
1994 budget, there may be changes in the composition of the 
coalition. 
  Among the ruling coalition parties, Komeito Secretary 
General 
Yuichi Ichikawa has proposed a "council on basic issues" for the 
ruling parties to discuss policies, while the Social Democratic 
Party of Japan and Sakigake [Harbinger] are suspicious of this 
proposal. Under the circumstances, Aichi's remark is expected 
to create a stir. 

</TEXT>

