<H3> <TI>   Protests of F-15 Crash in Okinawa Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protests of F-15 Crash in Okinawa Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ishikawa City Mayor Protests </H4>

<F P=102> OW0704062294 Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO in Japanese 6 Apr 94 Evening 
Edition p 7--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0704062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ishikawa -- At a news conference on the morning of 
6 April, Ishikawa City Mayor Takashi Hirakawa issued a statement 
protesting the crash of a U.S. Air Force F-15 fighter. He 
stated: "A jet belonging to the U.S. Kadena Air Base crashed 
during exercises into the Miyamori Elementary School in Ishikawa 
City 35 years ago. The accident killed 17 people, including 11 
school children, and injured 121. Having experienced a tragic 
accident in the past, we cannot look on the latest crash 
nonchalantly. We will file a strong protest against the U.S. 
forces and the Japanese Government, and will strongly demand 
they take carefully thought-out measures to prevent similar 
accidents." The Ishikawa City Government intends to send 
letters of protest about the accident to ten officials, 
including the prime minister, the ambassador to the United 
States, the airbase commander, and the prefectural governor. 

</TEXT>

