<H3> <TI>   Business Leader on Economy, Hosokawa Cabinet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Business Leader on Economy, Hosokawa Cabinet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604064094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 6 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0604064094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 6 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Masaru Hayami, chairman of Keizai Doyukai [Japan 
Association of Corporate Executives], commented on the economic 
situation at a news conference held on 5 April. He stated: 
"The economic situation will soon hit bottom, then take a turn 
for the better." With regard to the recent appreciation of the 
yen, he indicated there will be no further rise in the yen's 
value, saying: "The United States is not in a position to wish 
for the depreciation of the dollar." Concerning criticism about 
the Hosokawa administration in connection with the issue of 
Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa's loan, Hayami indicated his 
hope for the continuation of the Hosokawa administration, 
stating: "I think it is premature to say the Hosokawa 
administration's role is over." 

</TEXT>

