<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Source: Kim Chong-il Given Full Power </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Source: Kim Chong-il Given Full Power </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704093394 Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Apr 94 
Evening Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0704093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ho Chong-man, responsible vice chairman of the 
General Association of Korean Residents in Japan [Chongnyon], 
said he believes "DPRK (North Korean) President Kim Il-song has 
delegated full power -- political, economic, and military -- to 
Workers' Party of Korea Secretary Kim Chong-il." He made the 
remark in an address at a meeting of the Social Democratic Party 
of Japan's Japan-Korea Committee held at the First Dietmen's 
Hall on the morning of 5 April. 
  Vice Chairman Ho said he had talks with Secretary Kim 
Chong-il for about two hours when he visited North Korea from 15 
February to 1 March. Ho denied rumors that Kim had been 
seriously injured, saying "he was in excellent health." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

