<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Convention Plenary Session Reconvenes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Convention Plenary Session Reconvenes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Report on 5 Apr Session </H4>

<F P=102> BK0504124294 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 0630 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0504124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The plenary session of the National Convention 
[PSNC] resumed at 0900 this morning in the Central Meeting Hall 
of the president's residence compound on Ahlone Road, Yangon 
[Rangoon]. 
  The plenary session was attended by Lieutenant General Myo 
Nyunt, chairman of the National Convention Convening Commission, 
and commission members; U Aung Toe, chairman of the National 
Convention Convening Work Committee [NCCWC], and work committee 
members; Brigadier General Tin Aye, chairman of the National 
Convention Convening Management Committee, and committee 
members; national convention delegates; and local and foreign 
correspondents. 
  At the plenary session, U Khin Maung Htoo from the public 
service personnel delegate group acted as alternate chairperson 
while Dr. Than Nyunt; U Saw Philip, alias U Philip San; U San 
Tha Aung; U Mahn Ohn Maung; U Kan Nyunt; U Soe Maung; U Tin 
Maung; and U Sai Aung Htun acted as members of the Panel of 
Chairmen, while U Khin Maung Myint, director general of the 
NCCWC Office and the official in charge of the meetings, acted 
as secretary. 
  First, the secretary of the meeting announced the validity 
of 
the session as 645 out of 693 delegates attended. According to 
the agenda, the Panel of Chairmen of the National Convention 
presented a review and analysis of the suggestions submitted by 
the delegate groups at the PSNC to prescribe the fundamental 
principles related to the state, state structure, and head of 
state chapters which will be included in drawing up the 
constitution. Initially, Alternate U Khin Maung Htoo presented 
the review and analysis on the state chapter and Dr. Than Nyunt, 
member of the Panel of Chairmen, later continued the review and 
analysis on the same chapter. The plenary session recessed at 
1035. The afternoon session of the PSNC is currently in 
progress at the Central Meeting Hall of the president's 
residence compound on Ahlone Road, Yangon. 

</TEXT>

