Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Meeting Held with Sweden in Hanoi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Meeting Held with Sweden in Hanoi </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Paper Hails Visit </H4>

<F P=102> BK0704083794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704083794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of the official friendship visit to 
Vietnam by Swedish Prime Minister Carl Bildt, the paper NHAN DAN 
on 7 April carried an editorial entitled: "Strengthen the 
Relations of Friendship and Cooperation Between Vietnam and 
Sweden." The editorial says: 
  The world economic crisis has caused numerous difficulties 
for the Swedish economy. As a result, the Swedish Government, 
headed by Prime Minister Carl Bildt after the 1991 election, has 
cut its development aid to foreign countries. However, it has 
increased aid to our nation and has become the country with the 
largest volume of non-refundable aid to Vietnam. 
  The Swedish Government and businessmen have highly appraised 
Vietnam's renovation process and hailed the achievements 
recorded by our country in this regard. Our Swedish friends 
have also expressed their wish to expand cooperation with 
Vietnam and enhance the fine relations between the two countries. 
  The official visit to Vietnam by Swedish Prime Minister Carl 
Bildt is a significant event in the Vietnam-Swedish relations 
and is in line with Vietnam's open door foreign policy. 
  The Vietnamese people warmly welcome the first visit to 
Vietnam by the Swedish Prime Minister and wish him splendid 
success. Indeed, the visit will contribute to strengthening the 
friendship and cooperation between Vietnam and Sweden, thereby 
meeting the aspiration and interest of the two peoples and 
strengthening peace, stability, and development in the region. 
062300 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-5027 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas067_n_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-067 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Receives French Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Receives French Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0704104094 Hanoi VNA in English 0606 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0704104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 7 -- Vietnamese Minister of National 
Defence General Doan Khue received here yesterday a delegation 
of the institute of the high-ranking Military Research of France 
led by General Francois Bresson on a working visit to Vietnam. 
  Also present at the reception were deputy general staff of 
the Vietnam People's Army Lieut. Nguyen The Bon, and director of 
the high-ranking Military Institute Senior Lieut. General Nguyen 
Huu An. 
  French ambassador to Vietnam Jean-Francois Nugarede and 
military attache Lt. Col Daniel Schaeffer were also present. 
  During the reception, General Doan Khue expressed his hope 
that the delegation's visit will contribute to the promotion of 
the mutual understanding and cooperation between the two 
countries. 
  General Francois Bresson, for his part, expressed his 
admiration at the achievements recorded by the Vietnamese people 
and armed forces in their national construction. 
  While in Vietnam the French military delegation was informed 
of Vietnam's polices on military, foreign and economics and 
investment affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

