<F P=102>   BK0704073394 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ramos has made additional appointments for 
the Armed Forces. Major General Orlando Soriano of the 
Philippine Army will lead the Southern Command. He will replace 
Lieutenant General Thelmo Cunanan, who is going to retire on 14 
April. Brigadier Edgardo Batenga will be the new Northern Luzon 
Commander. He will replace Soriano. Batenga's replacement as 
5th Infantry Division chief is Brigadier General Romeo 
(Padiernos). 
  Nineteen officials, including General Lisandro Abadia, will 
officially retire this year. 

</TEXT>

