<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Killing of Former Guerrilla Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Killing of Former Guerrilla Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    CPP Claims Killing </H4>

<F P=102> BK0704083994 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Communist Party of the Philippines [CPP] has 
claimed responsibility for the assassination of former communist 
guerrilla commander Leopoldo Mabilangan, alias Comrade Hector. 
The Philippine News and Features interviewed another communist 
guerrilla chieftain who is still active in the movement about 
the Mabilangan assassination. Gregorio Rosal, alias Comrade 
Roger, spokesman of the CPP in southern Tagalog and Luzon, told 
the news organization that Mabilangan was ordered killed for his 
criminal and anti- revolutionary activities. Mabilangan had 
been charged of extortion and other criminal activities, 
including kidnapping for ransom. He was expelled from the CPP 
in February last year. 
  Mabilangan and a bodyguard was shot dead in front of a 
parish 
church in Batangas on Easter Sunday [2 April]. Mabilangan was 
to act as principal sponsor in a wedding ceremony. Three other 
people, including a traffic policeman, were wounded. 

</TEXT>

