<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Documents Exchanged on Cambodian Assistance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Documents Exchanged on Cambodian Assistance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704035694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0310 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704035694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 7 KYODO -- Japan will grant up to 500 
million yen in assistance to Cambodia to help it increase food 
production, the Foreign Ministry said Thursday [7 April]. 
Japanese Ambassador to Cambodia Yukio Imagawa and Cambodia's 
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Prince Norodom 
Sirivut exchanged documents on the agreement in Phnom Penh, the 
ministry said. 
  The aid will be used to purchase fertilizers and 
agricultural 
machinery, it said. Food production in Cambodia is very slow 
because its economy was destroyed by years of war and because of 
lack of fertilizers and machinery, the ministry said. 
  The latest aid brings the total amount of Japanese 
grant-in-aid to Cambodia in fiscal 1993 to about 8.4 billion 
yen, it said. 

</TEXT>

