<DOCNO> FBIS4-5048 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas067_a_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-067 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tokyo, Moscow Agree on Sakhalin-Hokkaido Ferry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo, Moscow Agree on Sakhalin-Hokkaido Ferry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604122194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1024 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 6 KYODO -- Japanese and Russian 
shipping companies have agreed to open a ferry route between 
Sakhalin and two Japanese port cities in Hokkaido -- Otaru and 
Wakkanai -- in April 1995, a Transport Ministry official said 
Wednesday [6 April]. The agreement, which came after two days 
of talks ended in Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk Wednesday, also calls for 
serving the new ferry route on a trial basis in July, the 
official said. 
  The shipping talks were held under a February 1991 agreement 
between the Japanese and then Soviet governments. 
  The two sides are slated to meet again between late May and 
early June in Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk to negotiate details of the 
trial service, including how many and how long. 

</TEXT>

