<H3> <TI>   Bills To Relax Car Inspection Rules Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bills To Relax Car Inspection Rules Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704130394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1207 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0704130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 7 KYODO -- The Transport Ministry on 
Thursday [7 April] announced bills to relax car inspection 
regulations as part of government deregulation efforts. The 
deregulation involves the elimination of rules requiring a car 
inspection once every six months as well as a reduction in items 
required for annual and biennial car inspections. 
  The ministry plans to implement the latest measures next 
year, ministry officials said. 
  The ministry expects the scrapping of the six-month 
inspection requirements to save car owners an average 15,000 yen 
and the reduction in items for annual and biennial inspections 
to save them 4,000 yen and 8,000 yen, respectively, they said. 

</TEXT>

