<H3> <TI>   Committee Considers Moving Diet Outside Tokyo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Considers Moving Diet Outside Tokyo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0604130894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1249 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0604130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 6 KYODO -- An advisory committee has 
completed the outline of a report on transferring the Diet and 
other government facilities outside congested Tokyo, committee 
officials said Wednesday [6 April]. 
  The outline, set for release in June, suggested that such a 
transfer would enable Japan to "realize a land structure 
suitable for the 21st century." The issue of transferring the 
Diet outside the capital has been debated for years. 
  The panel said it would also serve to facilitate political 
and administrative reforms, including deregulation and 
decentralization of power. 
  The outline will serve as the basis for an intermediate 
report to be issued in June on the subject of the "significance 
and effect" of making such a transfer. Afterwards, the 
committee will come up with a master plan. 
  At the end of the month, a separate advisory panel will 
begin 
considering what conditions should be met before considering new 
sites for the Diet. Contenders include such cities as Sendai in 
northern Japan. 

</TEXT>

