<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Norwegian Party Condemns U.S. on Patriot Move </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Norwegian Party Condemns U.S. on Patriot Move </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0204105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1016 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0204105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 2 (KCNA) -- Dag Norum, 
international secretary of the Norwegian Communist Party, was 
interviewed by KCNA in Pyongyang on March 30. 
  He said that to remove the danger of a nuclear war and ease 
the tensions on the Korean peninsula where an acute military 
confrontation continues is an important question directly linked 
to peace and security of the world at present. 
  Charging that the United States is committing insincere act, 
deploying Patriot missiles in South Korea by reversing the 
agreed conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York, 
he said: "The Norwegian Communist Party strongly opposes the 
shipment of new mass destruction weapons to South Korea." 
  He held that the United States must not resort to 
"sanctions", but work for a peaceful solution of the Korean 
question through dialogue and negotiation. 
  "If the United States think it will be able to bring the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea to its knees by strength, 
it is a big mistake," he said, and added: "The United States 
must abandon its anachronistic dream." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

