<H3> <TI>   ROK-U.S. War Games on 4, 5 Apr Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK-U.S. War Games on 4, 5 Apr Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Moves Termed Provocative, Reckless </H4>

<F P=102> SK0704050594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0444 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0704050594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
on April 4 brought overseas-based E-3 early warning plane, FA-18 
pursuit-assault planes, AV-8 VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] 
assault planes and KC-135 tanker planes to South Korea for 
provocative joint air war exercises against the Northern half of 
Korea, military sources said. 
  Exercises, such as a surprise bombing on ground targets, air 
attack and support of ground attack, were staged with the skies 
above Chungju, Tanyang and Pyongchang as operational theatres. 
They involved hundreds of fighter-bombers, assault planes, 
observation planes and reconnaissance planes belonging to the 
U.S. Airforce in South Korea and the puppet Airforce. 
  In another development, the South Korean puppets on April 4 
and 5 fired shells and volleys of large-calibre machinegun and 
automatic rifle bullets into spots near the Demilitarized Zone 
in Yonchon and Paju Counties, Kyonggi Province, and Chorwon 
County, South Korean Kangwon Province. 
  On the 5th of April, formations of helicopter gunships and 
transport helicopters of the puppet Army staged missile strike 
and airlifting exercises, making low- and ultralow-altitude 
flights in the skies above Paju and Yonchon areas. 
  Warplanes mobilized in various air war games against the 
North which were staged in skies above South Korea in two days 
totaled more than 700. 
  Very ill-boding are provocative military moves of the U.S. 
imperialists and the South Korean puppets which are becoming all 
the more reckless. 
  They must act with discretion, clearly mindful of the 
seriousness of the tensions created on the Korean peninsula. 

</TEXT>

