<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Blames U.S. on Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0704110294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1033 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0704110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Chongnyon Chief Vice-Chairman on Current Situation Over </F>
`Nuclear Issue'" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Tokyo, April 5 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
Ho Chong-man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing 
Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon), on April 5 was invited to address a general 
meeting and a roundtable talk on Japan-Korea Affairs of the 
Japan-Korea Committee of the Japan Social Democratic Party 
(JSDP). 
  Referring to the current situation surrounding the "nuclear 
issue", Ho Chong-man said the United States is entirely to blame 
for the situation in which the agreed conclusions reached at the 
DPRK-U.S. contact in New York on Februray 25 and the Feb. 15 
agreement between the DPRK and the International Atomic Energy 
Agency had been reversed, and for the situation of the Korean 
peninsula which is rushing headlong to the brink of war. 
  He said that the "presidential statement" of the UN Security 
Council was another international pressure upon the DPRK and 
that such "threat" and "pressure" could never be a solution to 
the problem. 
  "The `nuclear issue' must be solved fairly in keeping with 
the special status of the DPRK in which it has temporarily 
suspended the effectuation of its announced withdrawal from the 
treaty on the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons," he said, 
expressing the hope that the JSDP would play a positive role to 
this end. 

</TEXT>

