<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
denounce the recent publication of a "presidential statement" by 
the UN Security Council [UNSC] urging the DPRK to accept an 
additional inspection by the International Atomic Energy Agency 
as a very wrong act contrary to the aim and principle of the UN 
charter. 
  Stating that the DPRK's "nuclear issue" is not a matter to 
be 
discussed by the UN Security Council, a news analyst of NODONG 
SINMUN says: 
  The DPRK is in a special status after temporarily suspending 
the effectuation of its declared withdrawal from the Nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty. Accordingly, it is not obliged to 
undergo routine and ad hoc inspections by the agency. 
  If the UN Security Council is willing to resolve the nuclear 
issue of the Korean peninsula, it should take issue with the 
United States that is laying hurdles in the way of the solution 
of the nuclear issue and wrecking peace and security with a huge 
quantity of nuclear weapons, and its underlings, the South 
Korean authorities. 
  When it caviled at the DPRK, the UN Security Council showed 
that it was applying a double standard and playing into the 
hands of the United States in its policy of stifling the DPRK. 
  It must bear due responsibility for the consequences of its 
illegal dealing with the DPRK's "nuclear issue" against the aim 
and principle of the UN charter. 
  A news analyst of MINJU CHOSON warns that when the United 
States and its followers are further expanding their anti-DPRK 
pressure kickup, taking the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK to the 
international arena, the DPRK cannot but take an appropriate 
measure. 
  It is the will and invariable stand of the DPRK to maintain 
an independent policy and not to allow any unwarrantable 
demands, declares the paper. 

</TEXT>

