<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK `Suppression' of Trade Unions Condemned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0604105894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1040 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0604105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Crackdown on Trade Unions Condemned"--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- The Kim Yong-sam 
group's suppression of South Korean trade unions is under fire 
in MINJU CHOSON today. 
  The analyst says: 
  The South Korean puppets a few days ago arrested a working 
member, the organizational section chief and two other core 
members of the Ulsan-based Hyundai Heavy Industries Trade Union 
on the suspicion of the violation of "the National Security Law" 
(NSL). Meanwhile, the puppet Labour Ministry put forward "a 
policy of intensifying investigation into the operation" of 
trade unions and announced that it "would be promoted from the 
viewpoint of reforms." 
  These facts clearly show how craftily and viciously the foxy 
traitor Kim Yong-sam is working to suppress trade unions. 
  The suppression is aimed at keeping the workers from being 
awakened and organized and from taking a massive action through 
trade unions. 
  Last year in which the traitor came to power, 2,590 workers 
were put on the "want" list and more than 3,000 workers were 
fired unjustifiably for their involvement in the labour movement. 
  As if it were not enough, the Kim Yong-sam group arrested 
core elements of trade unions by invoking the notorious "NSL" 
and is going to intensify "investigation into the operation" of 
trade unions. This reveals their consciousness of crisis. 
  The reality proves that, with the Kim Yong-sam group left 
alone, it is impossible for the South Korean workers to win the 
right to existence, let alone democratic freedom. 
  The South Korean workers will vigorously struggle to 
overthrow the traitor Kim Yong-sam engaged in anti-popular 
misrule and establish an independent, democratic government, 
concludes the analyst. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

