<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Accused of `Scheme' for Nuclear Power </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0704051794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0458 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0704051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Japan's Nuclear Armament Reaches Danger Line" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- A fast breeder reactor 
Monju built in Tsuruga, Fukui Prefecture, Japan, went into 
operation on April 5, reported NHK. 
  The commissioning of Monju fully reveals Japan's undisguised 
scheme to become a nuclear power by securing a large quantity of 
plutonium for itself and manufacturing nuclear weapons any 
moment. 
  It is an open challenge to the Korean people and the Asian 
and world people who are desirous of peace. 
  Japan is already possessed of elements for the manufacture 
of 
nuclear bombs including electronic explosive devices and their 
technologies. Before commissioning Monju it launched the large 
long-range rocket "H-2" in February this year. Its nuclear 
armament has now reached the danger line. 
  Nevertheless, the Japanese authorities are now crying for 
"additional inspection" and "economic sanctions" over the 
fictitious "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. This is as base as a 
thief crying "stop thief " the Japanese authorities must give up 
their criminal nuclear design, mindful of the grave consequences 
to be entailed by their moves to make Japan a nuclear power. 

</TEXT>

