<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery Anniversary Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery Anniversary Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0504043794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0426 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0504043794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- It is 40 years since 
the revolutionary martyrs' cemetery was built. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song saw to it that the 
cemetery was built on April 5, 1954. 
  The cemetery is located on top of the Jujak peak of Mt. 
Taesong in Pyongyang. 
  Lying buried there are anti-Japanese revolutionary martyrs 
including Comrade Kim Chong-suk, an indomitable communist 
revolutionary fighter, who dedicated their precious lives to the 
anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and the struggle for the 
victory of the socialist cause under the wise leadership of 
President Kim Il-song. 
  In the cemetery there are a monument bearing the autograph 
of 
President Kim Il-song, bronze busts of martyrs, and a 
wreath-laying stand on which the medal of hero of the DPRK is 
embossed. 
  The cemetery was reconstructed on an expansion basis into a 
grand monumental edifice on the occasion of the 40th anniversary 
of the founding of the Workers' Party of Korea (October 10, 
1985) under the energetic and meticulous guidance of the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The cemetery is a symbol of the deep trust and sense of 
obligation of President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il for 
the anti-Japanese revolutionary martyrs, and high appreciation 
of the exploits of the martyrs who remained loyal to the party 
and the leader, the country and the people till their last 
moments. 
  A meeting was held to mark the 40th anniversary of the 
establishment of the cemetery. 
  At the meeting, Pak Song-chol, Politburo member of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea and 
vice-president, conveyed a message of thanks of the WPK Central 
Committee to the officials and employees of the management 
office of the revolutionary martyrs' cemetery. 
  The message highly praises the officials and employees of 
the 
management office for their responsible management of the 
cemetery and education of people through the cemetery over the 
last 40 years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

