<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Sharp Increase' Said in Mar Inter-Korean Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Sharp Increase' Said in Mar Inter-Korean Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0604072294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0656 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0604072294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 6 (YONHAP) -- Despite lingering tension 
on the Korean peninsula, trade between South Korea and North 
Korea rose sharply in March, the National Unification Board 
(NUB) said Wednesday. 
  Last month, 68 inter-Korean deals worth 21.28 million U.S. 
dollars were approved by NUB. 
  This compares with 53 cases amounting to 14.77 million 
dollars in February. 
  The monthly total for March exceeded 20 million dollars for 
the first time since last August. 
  The sharp increase was caused by North Korea's expansion of 
imports to offset a shortage of materials. 
  Inter-Korean deals approved by NUB in the first quarter are 
forecast to rise 10.3 percent from the same period last year. 

</TEXT>

