<F P=103> SK0704095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yi Tong-sik from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] China has reasserted its position of opposing the 
deployment of Patriot missiles to the ROK. In a news briefing 
this afternoon, Wu Jianmin, spokesman for the PRC Foreign 
Ministry, said that it is not considered desirable to conduct 
any exercises or deploy missiles that would harm the security of 
the Korean peninsula, and that they [United States and the ROK] 
should refrain from conducting an act that would heighten 
tensions on the peninsula. 
  Spokesman Wu Jianmin said that regarding the recent reports 
on China's envoy for Kim Il-song's 82d birthday, China would not 
send a high-level envoy to North Korea. 

