<H3> <TI>   Industrial Complex Planned in Russia's Nakhodka </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Industrial Complex Planned in Russia's Nakhodka </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0404113594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0541 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0404113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 4 (YONHAP) -- The Korea-Russia Far East 
Siberia Association met Monday morning at the Korea Chamber of 
Commerce and Industry Building to discuss boosting cooperation. 
  The association is led by Maritime Province Governor 
Yevgeniy 
Nazdratenko of Russia and Chang Chi-hyok, chairman of South 
Korea's Kohap Group. 
  At the meeting, the association agreed to construct an 
industrial complex for Korean-Russian cooperation and an 
exclusive quay for South Korean ships at Vostochny port in the 
Nakhodka special economic zone. 
  The association will also recommend that the Governments of 
South Korea and Russia designate small special economic zones 
elsewhere in the Russian Far East and Siberia. 
  The association plans to obtain permission to establish a 
regular direct line between Seoul and Vladivostok and study ways 
to open another direct line between South Korea and Irkutsk, 
Novosibirsk and Kamchatka Provinces. 
  Meanwhile, the association decided to hold regular 
exhibitions of Korean goods in several Siberian and Far Eastern 
cities including Khabarovsk and Yuzhno Sakhalinsk as well as 
seminars and working-level talks between South Korean and 
Russian businesses. 

</TEXT>

