<F P=103> SK0404084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 4 (YONHAP) -- Regular air service will 
open between Seoul and Khabarovsk, Russia, in June and Asiana 
Airlines will fly the route once a week, Transportation Ministry 
officials said Monday. 
  In addition, Korean Air [KAL] and Asiana will increase 
flights between Seoul and Singapore to 14 times and five times a 
week, respectively, from mid-April. 
  KAL will expand service between Seoul and Manila to four 
times a week in mid-April and Asiana will begin flying the route 
three times weekly in mid-May. 
  Korean Air's service on the Seoul-Moscow-Amsterdam route 
will 
be divided into Seoul-Moscow and Seoul-Amsterdam routes in May. 
  The Transportation Ministry asked the two national carriers 
to cooperate in selling tickets and carrying passengers on the 
Seoul-Manila route to avoid excess competition, but the two 
airlines refused and will fly the route separately. 
  Korean Air and Asiana will begin working-level contacts on 
allowing passengers to use both airlines' tickets on domestic 
routes and cooperating in carrying international travelers. 

</TEXT>

