<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   South Chungchong Province Governor Resigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Chungchong Province Governor Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0604023394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0221 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0604023394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 6 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
accepted on Wednesday the resignation of Pak Tae-kwon, governor 
of South Chungchong Province, who recently created a public 
controversy over his alleged pre-election campaigning. 
  President Kim was briefed on the details of the controversy 
by his Senior Secretary for Governmental Affairs, Yi Ui-kun, and 
accepted the resignation, an official at Chongwadae 
[presidential office] said. 
  Kim is expected to appoint a replacement for Pak soon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

