<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hun Sen Bodyguard Said Killed in Kompong Cham </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hun Sen Bodyguard Said Killed in Kompong Cham </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0704082594 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 7 
Apr 94 pp 1, 5 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a reliable source, a group of 12 
unidentified persons opened fire on Nim Kimsam, killing him and 
wounding Hun Mav as the two were riding on a motorcycle. 
  The killing took place in Prek Tuok village, Khporp Ta Nguon 
commune, in Kompong Cham Province's Stoeng Trang District. 
  According to a report by Kompong Cham provincial officials, 
Nim Kimsam was en route to his home town to attend his younger 
sister's wedding. 
  No motive for the killing has been provided or affirmed by 
any source. Some sources say that Nim Kimsam was an Interior 
Ministry bodyguard -- part of Samdech Hun Sen's bodyguard group 
-- and that he was gunned down with AK rifles by the 
unidentified group of people while riding a motorcycle to visit 
friends in his hometown. 
  It has not yet been determined if Nim Kimsam's murder was 
motivated by revenge or something else. 
  The authorities are investigating to unmask the murderers 
and 
forward the files to the tribunal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

