  [Text] Netherlands Prime Minister Ruud Lubbers cut short 
his visit and left Jakarta for home this evening. The state 
guest earlier paid a farewell call on President and Mrs. Suharto 
before returning home. Minister and State Secretary Murdiono 
said Prime Minister Lubbers was originally scheduled to have a 
four-day stay in Indonesia. Lubbers had earlier been scheduled 
to meet tomorrow morning with Hartarto, coordinating minister 
for industry and trade; Saleh Afiff, coordinating minister for 
economy, finance, and development supervision; and Wardiman 
Joyonegoro, minister of education and culture. 

