<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Meeting With Netherlands Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Meeting With Netherlands Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ali Alatas-Kooijmans Talks Noted </H4>

<F P=102> BK0704104394 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Ali Alatas and his Netherlands 
counterpart held talks on the human rights issue during the 
latter's visit to Indonesia. The Netherlands foreign minister, 
Kooijmans, was accompanying Premier Ruud Lubbers on a state 
visit to Indonesia. 
  Ali Alatas told newsmen in Surabaya, East Java, yesterday 
that he explained to Kooijmans about various problems in the 
country, including the human rights and East Timor issues and 
efforts to resolve them. 
  On bilateral cooperation, Ali Alatas reiterated that 
economic 
ties between Indonesia and the Netherlands have proceeded 
smoothly, while the private sector from the two countries is 
involved in matters pertaining to the transfer of technology. 

