  [Text] A Myanmar [Burmese] delegation led by Brigadier 
General Abel, national planning and economic development 
minister, left Yangon [Rangoon] by Myanmar Airways International 
this evening to attend the GATT organization's ministerial 
meeting on the final agreement on Uruguay trade negotiations to 
be held in Marrakech, Morocco. 
  After attending the meeting, the minister, at the invitation 
of the Vietnamese Government, will attend the ministerial 
meeting on regional economic cooperation among Cambodia, China, 
Laos, Myanmar, Thailand, and Vietnam to be held in Hanoi. The 
meeting is jointly sponsored by the Asian Development Bank and 
the National Planning Committee. 

