<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Nuclear Issue, Perry's Remark </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Views Nuclear Issue, Perry's Remark </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0704055394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0400 GMT 7 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0704055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu said that it is hard 
to consider the North Korean nuclear issue a South-North issue 
because it has developed into an issue at the level of 
international cooperation since the UN Security Council took 
issued the president's statement. 
  While giving a briefing on the result of President Kim's 
recent visit to Japan and China at the Democratic Liberal 
Party's office today, Minister Han Sung-chu said the above and 
added that we should try to resolve the nuclear issue between 
South and North Korea through efforts between the International 
Atomic Energy Agency and North Korea and between the United 
States and North Korea. 
  Minister Han also said we should make efforts to remove the 
belief at home and abroad that the Korean peninsula is facing a 
crisis to prevent adverse influence upon our economy, including 
tourism, investment, and trade. He added that U.S. Secretary of 
Defense William Perry's recent remark that the United States 
would not hesitate to bring about war has been confirmed to be 
an exaggeration by reporters. 
  Regarding the Russian proposal for eight-party talks on the 
nuclear issue, Minister Han said that he basically welcomed 
[kibonjoguro hwanyonghanda] Russia's interest in the issue and 
that he would consult with countries concerned, watching their 
reactions. 

</TEXT>

