<F P=103> SK0804055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
and the South Korean puppets staged a provocative air war 
exercise against the North Wednesday with overseas-based KC-135 
refueling tankers, F-15 fighter-bombers and AV-8 VTOL [vertical 
takeoff and landing] assault planes and hundreds of 
fighter-bombers, assault planes and observation planes belonging 
to the U.S. Airforce in South Korea and the puppet airforce, 
military sources said. 
  The air war exercise in the skies above Chongju and Wonju 
was 
aimed at testing the capacity of the overseas-based warplanes of 
the U.S. Airforce and Marines in non-stop quick deployment in 
the operational airspace and surprise bombing on the North. 
  An overseas-based E-3 early warning plane, two RC-135 
strategic reconnaissance planes, U-2 high-attitude strategic 
reconnaissance plane, RV-1 tactical reconnaissance plane and 
three RF-4C airforce reconnaissance planes committed an aerial 
espionage on the frontline area, coastline area, the inland and 
strategic in-depth areas of the North. 
  Fifteen reconnaissance planes were involved in the aerial 
espionage on the North in the South Korean airspace that day. 

</TEXT>

