<H3> <TI>   ROK Student Strike on Market Opening Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Student Strike on Market Opening Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0510 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon) declared 
Thursday afternoon that students of more than 140 universities 
and colleges across South Korea would go on a strike all at once 
from April 8 in an effort to check a "parliamentary 
ratification" of the farm market opening and as an expression of 
protest against signing of the "Uruguay Round Accord" due in 
Morocco this month, a radio report from Seoul said. 
  Along with this, a more than 200-member "hunger-strike team 
of Hanchongnyon for national salvation" will launch into an 
indefinite hunger sit-down at the "National Assembly Hall" in 
Youido, Seoul, and fasting will be staged in different areas and 
at universities for an indefinite period, it announced. 
  Hanchongnyon took a vote on the farm market opening and the 
signing of the "Uruguay Round Accord" among 350,000 students of 
145 universities and colleges, and 90.5 percent of the voters 
expressed opposition to them. 

</TEXT>

