<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hanminjon Issues Statement on Reunification Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanminjon Issues Statement on Reunification Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0604140294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1035 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0604140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Cho Il-min, chief of 
the Pyongyang mission of the South Korean National Democratic 
Front (Hanminjon), issued a statement Tuesday on the lapse of 
one year since the great leader President Kim Il-song put 
forward the historic "10-point programme of the great unity of 
the whole nation for The Reunification of the country." 
  The statement says: 
  The internal and external situation urgently demands that 
the 
Korean nation implement on a higher level the ten-point 
programme of the great unity of the whole nation put forward by 
respected President Kim Il-song. 
  Now that the Kim Yong-sam regime is totally blocking the 
people's movement for independent reunification and persisting 
in confrontation with the North, the entire Koreans in the 
South, North and overseas must unite more closely than ever 
before, smash the separatist moves of the anti-reunification 
forces and make a breakthrough for reunification with their own 
efforts. 
  Especially, the people in the South must demand an immediate 
end to the anti-North nuclear racket and "international 
cooperation system" of the United States and its followers which 
may lead to a nuclear war on the Korean peninsula. 
  When the entire nation courageously rises up in struggle to 
implement the ten-point programme of the great unity of the 
whole nation under the leadership of general Kim Chong-il, 
closely rallied around President Kim Il-song, the lodestar of 
national reunification, a new phase for national reunification 
will be opened up. 
  The entire members of Hanminjon, together with the 70 
million 
compatriots in the South, North and overseas, will vigorously 
fight to valiantly smash the nuclear war provocations and 
separatist acts of the U.S. imperialists and the Kim Yong-sam 
group and promote peace and independent reunification of the 
country in hearty response to the ten-point programme of the 
great unity of the whole nation put forward by the great 
president. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

