<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Nuclear Reactors `Disguised' for Military Use </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Nuclear Reactors `Disguised' for Military Use </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804060094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0542 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Indictment Against Nuclear Warmaniacs"--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
describes the white paper recently issued by the Central 
Committee of the South Korean National Democratic Front 
(Hanminjon) on the nuclear arms development of the South Korean 
authorities as one more stern indictment against the nuclear 
warmaniacs. 
  The news analyst says: 
  According to the white paper, the South Korean puppets have 
long since promoted the development of nuclear weapons under the 
nuclear umbrella of the United States. 
  The heavy water reactor in Wolsong and the multipurpose 
research reactor in Taedok, South Korea, are, to all intents and 
purposes, military facilities for nuclear arms development 
disguised as "commercial" and "research" reactors. 
  The heavy water reactor in Wolsong is not for "generating 
electricity." It was introduced for the production of plutonium. 
The reactor's structure is so designed as to change spent 
nuclear fuel any moment without stopping its operation. 
  The multipurpose research reactor in Taedok can be easily 
remodeled into a reactor producing plutonium any moment. 
Moreover, it is closely attached to a semi-reprocessing 
facility. 
  It must not go unnoticed that nuclear arms development is 
being promoted in secrecy at South Korea's atomic reactors and 
research reactors which are claimed to be undergoing routine 
inspection by the International Atomic Energy Agency. 
  It is only too natural that Hanminjon raised a question why 
the IAEA, while taking issue with the pilot reactor of the 
North, had not published the results of its inspection of South 
Korea's heavy water reactor and multi-purpose research reactor 
used for military purposes, whose capacities are scores of times 
and several times greater than the North's. 
  The South Korean people are now fighting against war and 
nuclear weapons and resolutely rejecting the Kim Yong-sam 
bellicose group's development of nuclear weapons. They will mete 
out a punishment to the Kim Yong-sam group. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

