<H3> <TI>   KCNA Denounces Japan's Intelligence-Gathering </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Denounces Japan's Intelligence-Gathering </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804102494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1013 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Japan's Intelligence Gathering on Korea Denounced" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- Japan is intensifying 
intelligence gathering while strengthening military tieup with 
the United States and the South Korean puppets against the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  Commenting on this, MINJU CHOSON today says the Korean 
people 
cannot remain an onlooker to this but are keeping tabs on 
Japan's moves. 
  The analyst says: 
  The Japan defence agency has set it as a primary task to 
"increase the capacity of intelligence gathering.",it is putting 
fresh muscles into the system of gathering information on the 
Korean peninsula and training in secrecy information-gathering 
experts with the help of the U.S. CIA. 
  Though the Cold War has ended Japan is now showing extra 
zeal 
in gathering information about the DPRK and other countries by 
using even satellite photographs provided by the United States. 
This is a tell-tale sign of its preparations for overseas 
aggression. 
  The top political and military quarters of Japan are 
attempting to overpower the DPRK with strength in league with 
the United States and the South Korean puppets. This is an 
anachronistic and foolish design. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must clearly know that their 
scheme to fulfil their design of overseas aggression, 
intensifying information gathering against the DPRK, will lead 
them to destruction. 

</TEXT>

