<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- A ten-day film show 
opened in Korea to celebrate the 15th of April. 
  Showing in the period are documentary films on the history 
of 
the revolutionary activities of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song, including "The Leader Is the Great Father of Our 
People" and "The Great Leader Has Opened a Broad Avenue for 
Bumper Crops", and feature films, including "The Star of Korea" 
(parts 1-10), "The Sun of the Nation" (parts 1-5) and "The 
Nation and Destiny" (follow-ups). 
  The films impressively show the course of the revolutionary 
struggle of the respected leader, the national pride and honor 
of the Korean people dynamically advancing under his leadership 
and the superiority of the Korean-style socialist system centred 
on the masses. 
  Opening ceremonies took place in provincial, city and county 
seats Thursday. 

