<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Life, Death of Revolutionary Fighter Remembered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Life, Death of Revolutionary Fighter Remembered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0504223394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1523 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0504223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- A national memorial 
service took place here Tuesday on the tenth anniversary of the 
death of O Paek-yong, a communist revolutionary fighter who was 
intensely loyal to the great leader President Kim Il-song, (on 
April 6, 1984). 
  O Paek-yong was a steadfast communist revolutionary fighter 
who fought all his life for the freedom and independence of the 
country and the accomplishment of the cause of socialism and 
communism and a courageous and talented military commanding 
officer who performed great feats in the revolutionary wars 
against U.S. and Japanese imperialism. 
  Choe Kwang, Politburo member of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea and chief of the general staff of the 
Korean People's Army, in his memorial address referred to the 
brilliant life of O Paek-yong and precious feats he performed in 
struggle. O was born into a poor peasant's family in Hoeryong 
county, North Hamgyong Province, on October 24, 1914, he joined 
in the revolutionary struggle in the 1930 and firmly defended 
the great leader politically and ideologically and with his life 
as an ordinary soldier, then a platoon leader, a company 
commander and a regimental commander in the whole period of the 
anti-Japanese armed struggle. 
  After the liberation of the country he worked hard to 
strengthen the People's Armed Forces and defend the gains of 
revolution from the aggression of the enemies, upholding 
President Kim Il-song's line of Army building and, during the 
fatherland liberation war, made a great contribution to 
repelling the invasion of the U.S. imperialists and defending 
the independence of the country as a divisional commander of the 
Korean People's Army. 
  Later, holding important posts of the Ministry of Interior, 
the Ministry of National Defence, the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea, the Central People's Committee and the 
National Defence Commission, he performed big feats in defending 
the headquarters of the Korean revolution and implementing the 
party's military line of self-reliant defense. 
  In the memorial address Choe Kwang said the life of O 
Paek-yong was a brilliant life of a communist revolutionary who 
dedicated his all to the party and the leader, the country and 
the people and the accomplishment of the cause of socialism and 
communism, and the intense loyalty to the party and the leader, 
a high degree of revolutionary spirit and devoted services for 
and modesty toward the people which ran through his whole life 
serve as a valuable example for all the party members and 
working people. 
  Attending the memorial service were O Chin-u, member of 
presidium of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee 
and minister of People's Armed Forces, Yi Chong-ok and Pak 
Song-chol, Politburo members of the WPK Central Committee and 
vice-president, Kim Pyong-sik, chairman of the C.C. [Central 
Committee], the Korean Social Democratic Party and 
vice-president, and other senior party and government officials 
and anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters. 
  Papers here today dedicate articles to the occasion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

