<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antitank Missiles Seized in Siem Reap Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Antitank Missiles Seized in Siem Reap Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0804105694 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1001 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0804105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP April 8 -- Four sets of anti-tank 
missile were seized in Siem Reap Province on April 5. Police 
said the four missiles known as "Bruss" were found in a boot of 
a taxi driving from Banteay Meanchey to Siem Reap. One man on 
board, suspected to be an owner of the missiles, was arrested 
when the police found the missiles at their checkpoint. 
  The taxi driver Yoeun Yang, 43, said the arrested man had 
ordered him to pick up a well-wrapped package, in which the 
missiles were found, at a place in Banteay Meanchey Province. 
  Besides the arrested man, there were one woman and two 
children on board. 
  Police said the four missiles were expected to be used for 
destroying tanks of the Regional Military Unit 4 stationed in 
Siem Reap Town. 
  Chea Sophat, the two-star police general, said he believed 
that the missiles, if not found, would have been used for not 
only destroying tanks but also for other purposes. 

</TEXT>

