BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, April 7 (KPL) -- Prime Minister of the 
Lao PDR [Lao People's Democratic Republic] Khamtai Siphandon, on 
April 5, received at Prime Minister's Office Mr. Phan Van Khai, 
president of the Vietnamese-Lao Cooperation Committee on 
official visit here. 
  On this occasion Mr. Phan Van Khai informed Prime Minister 
Khamtai Siphandon about the result of the 16th session of the 
Lao and Vietnamese cooperation committees and expressed thanks 
for the warm reception given by Prime Minister Khamtai Siphandon. 
  Vietnamese vice prime minister highly valued the many sided 
successes of the Lao people in the implementation of the 
renovation policy under the able leadership of the Lao People's 
Revolutionary Party currently headed by President Khamtai 
Siphandon. He also wished the fraternal Lao people still greater 
success. 
  Prime Minister Khamtai Siphandon, for his part, highly 
valued 
the visit of the high level delegation of Vietnam, considering 
it as a contribution to the development and strengthening of the 
friendly relations, special solidarity and all-round cooperation 
between the two nations. The Lao prime minister reaffirmed that 
the Lao PDR and the SR [Socialist Republic] of Vietnam enjoyed a 
long standing friendly relation and that the Vietnamese party, 
government and people would still provide assistance and 
cooperation to the Lao PDR. 

</TEXT>

