<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Accusations of KR Support Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodian Accusations of KR Support Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Prasong: Not Good for Relations </H4>

<F P=102> BK0704151194 Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 in Thai 
1200 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry is waiting for facts from the 
Cambodian prime ministers concerning the accusation by the 
Cambodian foreign minister about Thailand supporting the Khmer 
Rouge [KR] . 
  Foreign Minister Squadron Leader Prasong Sunsiri was asked 
by 
news reporters about Cambodian Foreign Minister Prince Norodom 
Sirivut's charge, which he made when he was in Malaysia that 
Thailand supported the Khmer Rouge and that there are pictures 
substantiating the charge. Prasong told reporters that he had 
instructed the Thai ambassador in Phnom Penh to seek a meeting 
with the Cambodian prime ministers in order to get facts from 
them so the Thai Government could take a proper course of 
action. Prasong said he did not understand why Prince Norodom 
Sirivut did not tell Thailand directly when he visited Thailand 
last time. 
  [Begin recording] [Prasong, in progress] ... this is not 
good for our relations -- existing and future relations. I will 
wait for information from the ambassador. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Prince Sirivut said he brought up 
this matter when he was in Malaysia. He said he wanted Malaysia 
to convey his concern to Thailand as Malaysia is an ASEAN friend 
of Thailand. 
  [Prasong] Why didn't he discuss it with us when he was in 
Thailand? We would like to ask him this question? [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

