<H3> <TI>   President Kim Talks With Japan's Hosokawa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kim Talks With Japan's Hosokawa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804112294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1115 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 8 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
had a telephone conversation with outgoing Japanese Prime 
Minister Morihiro Hosokawa Friday afternoon, in which Kim 
consoled the resigning premier. 
  The telephone talks lasted about 15 minutes beginning 6 P.M. 
It was called by Hosokawa. 
  The Japanese prime minister explained to President Kim about 
the background that led him to decide to resign as premier and 
thanked the president for the cooperation Kim showed to him. 
  President Kim said there would be no change in his 
friendship 
with and trust in Prime Minister Hosokawa, which he said had 
been cemented through mutual visits and summit talks. 

</TEXT>

