<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Meeting With Sweden Continues in Hanoi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Meeting With Sweden Continues in Hanoi </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Bildt Meets Leaders 7 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> BK0804014394 Hanoi VNA in English 1430 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0804014394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 7 -- Swedish Prime Minister Carl 
Bildt arrived here this morning for an official friendship visit 
to Vietnam as guest of Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet. 
  He was welcomed in a state ceremony at the Presidential 
Palace by Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet, Foreign Minister Nguyen 
Manh Cam, Mayor of Hanoi Le At Hoi and other Vietnamese ranking 
officials. Swedish Ambassador to vietnam Mats Aberg and members 
of the diplomatic corps and representatives of international 
organizations in Hanoi were also present. Speaking at the 
ceremony Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet thanked the Swedish 
Government and people for their great support and assistance to 
the Vietnamese people. For his part Prime Minister Carl Bildt 
stressed that his visit was a landmark of a new era in the 
relationship between the two countries. He reaffirmed that the 
Swedish Government and people would continue their aid to 
Vietnam, thus to contribute to its economic renovation. Later 
P.M. Carl Bildt and his party attended the inaugural ceremony of 
household electric appliances centre in Hanoi, a joint venture 
between Vietnam and Electrolux of Sweden. In the afternoon, a 
number of ranking officials in the Swedish delegation met with 
representatives of the State Planning Committee, the State 
Committee for Cooperation and Investment, and the Ministry of 
Trade. During these meetings, the two sides exchanged views on 
possibilities of broadening the cooperation and investment and 
economic exchanges between Vietnam and Sweden in conformity with 
the new situation. Yesterday, the Swedish prime minister and his 
party arrived in Ho Chi Minh City, beginning a three-day 
official friendship visit to Vietnam. The same day, mayor of 
the city Truong Tan Sang paid a courtesy visit to Mr. Carl 
Bildt, during which he informed the Swedish guests of the 
socio-economic situation, especially the achievements recorded 
by the people of the city in the current renovation process. In 
the evening, mayor Truong Tan Sang gave a banquet in honour of 
Swedish Prime Minister Carl Bildt and his party. Earlier, the 
Swedish prime minister attended a ceremony to inaugurate a 
mobile telephone system which started in early 1994. The system 
were installed with equipment made by Ericsson of Sweden at a 
cost of more than USD 6 million. 

</TEXT>

